This paper deals with dynamic pricing in combinatorial markets, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic economics (cs.EC). The paper also involves the characterization of optimal allocations in multi-demand markets, which is related to the study of allocation algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper proposes a poly-time algorithm for up to 3 multi-demand buyers, which is a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
